==English==
[[Image:Irony.jpg|thumb|right|An example of situational irony]]
===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]]: /'airɒni/
===Noun===
'''irony'''
#A [[statement]] that, when taken in context, may actually mean the [[opposite]] of what is written [[literally]]
# ''Colloq.''  The quality or state of an event being both [[coincidental]] and [[contradictory]] in a [[humorous]] or [[poignant]] and extremely [[improbable]] way.
# ''Colloq.''  An [[unfortunate]] and [[coincidental]] turn of events that could have been avoided had all parties involved known more.

===Examples===
A charity for ethnic refugees money creates a trust fund for itself, some of the money in the trust fund is invested in arms companies, who supply arms to the dictators of the countries of some of the refugees origin. The dictators happen to use their army to ethnically cleanse their lands of these very refugees. The profit made from arms sales of arms used to expell these refugees is going to the refugees via the charity.

